        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 175°C fan. Grease and line a 20 x 30 cm rectangular tin. Whisk the {{vegetable-oil}}, {{eggs}}, {{pumpkin}} puree, and {{vanilla-extract}} together in a large bowl. Stir in the {{light-brown-sugar}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until just combined. Pour into the tin and bake for 28 to 32 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tin completely before frosting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Frost and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} until smooth. Beat in the cold {{cream-cheese}} until just combined. Add the {{icing-sugar}} and {{vanilla-extract}} and beat briefly until smooth. Do not overbeat. Spread evenly over the cooled sponge. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to firm the frosting before cutting into 20 bars.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
